<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">electrae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">There's a tool out there on the web called Guild Magic which lets you create guilds and let people add themselves to your guild roster.  Wonderful tool(http://www.guildmagic.com).<P>Anyway, they have over 12,000 characters registered now.  No surprise the #1 most popular character is druid.  #2 is warrior and #3 is cleric.<P>It doesn't show you how many of those clerics are mostly unplayed alts and how many are actively played main characters unfortunately. <P>Just found this to be quite an interesting piece of information!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Panteroo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aye.. we are in the process of putting our guild in there for ease of use, tracking, updating etc...<P>found it very slick to use and pretty cool! If only we could hang a sign that said "Tank and Cleric heavy guild desperately seek Enchanters!!"  LOL<P> <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Panteroo</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Apallohadas Fayweaver</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hmm...12,000 characters in there?<P>300,000 subscriptions<BR>8 characters potential per subscription<BR>2.4 million potential character<BR>----------------<P>Don't think that's enough to say that clerics are the third most popular class. Maybe in that system yes.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">KamuelaTZ</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yeah, just like on the TZ board there is a poll and the most popular class is warrior. It's only because a twink warrior is brutal in pvp. It would be interesting to see a compilation from Verant on class/level in increments of 10. The only assumption I feel comfortable making is that every poll will show bards underplayed at upper levels.<P>Cleric is second highest, haven't figured that one out yet. I think there are always a lot of low clerics out there because people want rez. Then they play a cleric and burn out by 20 because it is so one dimensional and they want the 31337 skillz of their druid/necro.<P>------------------<BR>Teir' Dal Vicar<BR>Tallon Zek</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Arturo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Apallohadas,<P>Someone slept through random sampling in stats class in college didnt they  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif">.<P>------------------<BR>Arturo Fuente<BR>60th High Priest of Mithaniel Marr<BR>Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Arturo:<BR><B>Apallohadas,<P>Someone slept through random sampling in stats class in college didnt they   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif">.<P></B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Well, I never agreed with those random sample figures. It's all about location. If I were to go to say...Downtown Detroit, MI and do a random sample on gun control, drug usage and car theft, I am sure I would get a totally different set of statistics than if I went to say Beverly Hills, CA.<P>Poll 100 random single women about abortion and poll 100 random married women, then poll 100 single mothers and 100 married mothers and I am sure you will get 4 different results.<P>Could just be that that site (which I have never heard of) happened to get a cleric heavy response.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aquinas</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"><B>Someone slept through random sampling in stats class in college didnt they</B><P>The key word is "random."  A self-selected group like the folks who use a particular web site is almost certainly not a random sample.  That's why most web-site polls you see are about as informative as a horoscope.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Arturo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well, yes.  Sampling does take into account +/- percentages of error or aka Confidence Level.  You are correct sometimes it could be weighted or geograpical.  But usually a good statistician will include anything that may skew the numbers.  <P><BR>ps.  was only jabbin Apall.  I had my fair share of days sleepin in stats class =P.<P>------------------<BR>Arturo Fuente<BR>60th High Priest of Mithaniel Marr<BR>Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mahtan Honorshield</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Arturo said:  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>But usually a good statistician will include anything that may skew the numbers. <HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Like using only people in guilds? I am sure that this skews the numbers noticably...:-)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">desmodus</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Terris Thule has a plethora of Warriors and Druids and not enough clerics.<P>I would guess that clerics are probably 5th or 6th most popular on our server.<P>Normally if you do a who all class at peak hours you get half the server as playing druids hehe (or so it seems)<P>in order of appearance generally seems to go something like this:<P>1. druids<BR>2. warriors<BR>3. wizards<BR>4. mage<BR>5. monk<BR>6. ranger<BR>7. cleric<BR>8. paladine<BR>9. rogue<BR>10. shaman<BR>11. enchanter<BR>12. bard<BR>13. shadow knight<P>And clerics are either above 40 or lower than 20 for the most part.  I guess once you can get past 20 you can do anything and so stick with it...not sure my since my cleric just hit lvl 9 hehe</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">electrae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Talk about skewed stats, doing a /who is very misleading since /roleplay or /anon hides a lot of clerics and druids and wizards.<P>Actually, Therris Thule also has clerics as the number 3 class:<BR> <A HREF="http://www.guildmagic.com/server_stats.cfm?ID=15" TARGET=_blank>http://www.guildmagic.com/server_stats.cfm?ID=15</A> <P>Lookup up your own server here: <A HREF="http://www.guildmagic.com/find_character.cfm" TARGET=_blank>http://www.guildmagic.com/find_character.cfm</A> <P>So far on every server I've checked clerics are #3.  Druids always seem to be #1 and warriors #2.  Interesting!<P>Oh, found stats for all the servers and breakdown by class/level.  Interesting druids seem to be fairly evenly distributed between all level ranges, except the bottom levels. <A HREF="http://eq.guildmagic.com/site_stats.cfm" TARGET=_blank>http://eq.guildmagic.com/site_stats.cfm</A> <BR> <A HREF="http://eq.guildmagic.com/class_stats.cfm?class_id=3" TARGET=_blank>http://eq.guildmagic.com/class_stats.cfm?class_id=3</A> <BR>Clerics distributions are somewhat bumpier: <A HREF="http://eq.guildmagic.com/class_stats.cfm?class_id=2" TARGET=_blank>http://eq.guildmagic.com/class_stats.cfm?class_id=2</A>   Either there's a lot of new clerics being made, or else interest in them tends to drop off as they go up levels.<P>Warriors show even worse downward stair stepping than clerics.  So that tends to argue they get left behind a lot in favor of other classes.<P>Interesting to look at the trends and conjecture.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><p>[This message has been edited by electrae (edited 03-27-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
